# React Frontend Rules

## Language & Framework
- React 18 with TypeScript
- Vite for build tooling
- Plain CSS (no Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS)
- React Router for navigation

## Components
- Use functional components with hooks
- Keep components under 150 lines
- Co-locate CSS files with components (Component.tsx + Component.css)
- Use data-testid attributes for E2E test selectors

## TypeScript
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Define shared types in src/types/index.ts
- Use strict mode — no any types

## State Management
- Use React Context for global state (CartContext)
- Use useState for local component state
- Use useMemo/useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Extract complex state logic into custom hooks (src/hooks/)

## API Layer
- All API calls go through src/api/client.ts
- Use async/await over .then() chains
- Handle loading and error states in every data-fetching component

## Styling
- Use BEM-like class naming (.component-name, .component-name__element)
- Keep styles scoped to their component
- Use CSS custom properties for shared values (colors, spacing)
